HOW THE c3 SWAP AFFECTS DISJOINT PAIR PRODUCTS
======================================================================

  Example 1 (dH=2):
    Subset S = (1, 4, 5, 6)
    Lost c3 [1, 2, 4] (cap S = 2):
      Disjoint c5 [0, 3, 5, 6, 7]: mult 1->3 (delta=2)
    Lost c3 [2, 5, 6] (cap S = 2):
      Disjoint c5 [0, 1, 3, 4, 7]: mult 1->3 (delta=2)
    Gained c3 [1, 2, 5] (cap S = 2):
      Disjoint c5 [0, 3, 4, 6, 7]: mult 3->1 (delta=-2)
    Gained c3 [2, 4, 6] (cap S = 2):
      Disjoint c5 [0, 1, 3, 5, 7]: mult 3->1 (delta=-2)

  Example 2 (dH=2):
